    "discriminators": [
     "The COMPUTERS catch-all — and in practice it is dominated by ONE real sound: the machine's IDLE BED. Case, CPU and PSU fans produce a quiet, STATIONARY, broadband hiss with a faint blade-passing tone from the rotor. Hence the sustained_noise morphology and the stationarity prior, held at deliberately LOW weight so it never over-asserts over a genuine sibling.",
     "The subcategory is nonetheless semantic_only, and honestly so: a computer's fan bed is acoustically INDISTINGUISHABLE from MACHFan or an AMBOffc room tone. It is the same fan. Only text ('PC', 'laptop', 'CPU', 'desktop', 'mainframe') can commit it.",
